Note: Makefile Semantic Analyzer - Static analysis of GNU Make build files
Note: Part of the Translation universal language translation system
Note: -
Note: Performs a real two-phase static analysis over the parser AST produced by
Note: makefile_parser.runa:
Note:   Phase 1 (collect): walk every top-level statement and record every
Note:     target name, every defined variable name (assignments + define blocks),
Note:     every .PHONY declaration, and every include file.
Note:   Phase 2 (validate): re-walk the statements and check that prerequisite
Note:     references resolve to a known target or an on-disk source convention,
Note:     that $(VAR)/${VAR} references resolve to a defined or built-in make
Note:     variable, that recipe lines are well-formed, that no target is defined
Note:     twice with single-colon rules, and that .PHONY entries name real
Note:     targets.
Note: -
Note: The AST node layout consumed here is fixed by makefile_parser.runa and is
Note: documented inline at each accessor. All nodes are raw heap structs whose
Note: first 8-byte word is the NODE_* kind tag.

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/makefile/makefile_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrimitive
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Kind Constants (mirror makefile_parser.runa)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant NODE_MAKEFILE as Integer is 1000
Constant NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT as Integer is 1001
Constant NODE_TARGET_RULE as Integer is 1002
Constant NODE_RECIPE_LINE as Integer is 1003
Constant NODE_CONDITIONAL as Integer is 1004
Constant NODE_INCLUDE_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 1005
Constant NODE_EXPORT_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 1006
Constant NODE_DEFINE_BLOCK as Integer is 1007
Constant NODE_SPECIAL_TARGET as Integer is 1008
Constant NODE_FUNCTION_CALL as Integer is 1009
Constant NODE_VARIABLE_REFERENCE as Integer is 1010
Constant NODE_TEXT as Integer is 1011

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ANALYZER STATE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The analyzer threads six lists through the two-phase walk: target_names (every
target string declared by a rule), variable_names (every variable name defined
by an assignment or define block), phony_targets (every name listed under
.PHONY), errors and warnings (diagnostic message strings), and
undefined_targets (prerequisite names that resolved to no target). Flat string
lists keep membership tests cheap and let the driver read diagnostics directly
after analysis without any internal-layout knowledge. The struct is six 8-byte
slots = 48 bytes.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MakefileSemanticAnalyzer":
    target_names as Integer        Note: List of declared target-name strings
    variable_names as Integer      Note: List of defined variable-name strings
    phony_targets as Integer       Note: List of names declared under .PHONY
    errors as Integer              Note: List of error message strings
    warnings as Integer            Note: List of warning message strings
    undefined_targets as Integer   Note: List of unresolved prerequisite names
End Type

@Reasoning:
Allocates a 48-byte analyzer with six freshly-created lists so every analysis
run starts with empty collection and diagnostic state. Returns 0 on allocation
failure so callers can guard.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_makefile_semantic_analyzer" returns Integer:
    Let analyzer be proc allocate from Layout with 48
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let target_names be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 0, target_names

    Let variable_names be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 8, variable_names

    Let phony_targets be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 16, phony_targets

    Let errors be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 24, errors

    Let warnings be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 32, warnings

    Let undefined_targets be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_integer from Memory with analyzer, 40, undefined_targets

    Return analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Releases the analyzer struct. The six lists are borrowed by callers that read
diagnostics after analysis, so only the 48-byte struct is freed here; callers
own the analysis lifetime.
@End Reasoning
Process called "destroy_makefile_semantic_analyzer" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with analyzer
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SMALL ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Reads a node's NODE_* kind tag from offset 0. Null-guards the node so callers
can dispatch on the result without a separate null check.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_kind_of" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_integer from Memory with node, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic error message on the analyzer's error list (offset 24).
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_makefile_validation_error" takes analyzer as Integer, error_message as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let errors be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 24
    proc list_append from List with errors, error_message
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic warning message on the analyzer's warning list (offset 32).
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_makefile_validation_warning" takes analyzer as Integer, warning_message as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let warnings be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 32
    proc list_append from List with warnings, warning_message
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Linear membership test over a list of string pointers. Returns 1 when needle is
string-equal to any element, 0 otherwise. Used for target / variable / phony
lookups during validation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "string_list_contains" takes string_list as Integer, needle as Integer returns Integer:
    If string_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If needle is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from List with string_list
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let element be proc list_get from List with string_list, index
        If element is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with element, needle
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BUILT-IN MAKE VARIABLES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
GNU Make predefines a set of variables (compiler/tool names, default flags,
automatic variables) that are always available without an explicit assignment.
A reference to one of these must not be reported as undefined. The set checked
here is the standard implicit-rule variable family plus the automatic
variables; an unknown variable that is not in this set and not assigned in the
makefile is the signal for an undefined-variable warning.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_builtin_make_variable" takes variable_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If variable_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Tool / program name variables
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CC" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CXX" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "AR" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "AS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "LD" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "RM" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "MAKE" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "SHELL" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Standard flag variables
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CXXFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CPPFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "LDFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "ARFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "LDLIBS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Automatic variables (the one-byte names recorded by reference scanning)
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "@" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "^" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "?" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "|" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "%" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Make special variables
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "MAKEFLAGS" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "MAKEFILE_LIST" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "CURDIR" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with variable_name, "VPATH" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CHARACTER UTILITY
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 when text contains the byte target_char at least once, 0 otherwise.
Used for prerequisite shape checks ('.' extension, '/' path, '$' reference)
without allocating a substring.
@End Reasoning
Process called "contains_char" takes text as Integer, target_char as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, index
        If ch is equal to target_char:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VARIABLE-REFERENCE EXTRACTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Extracts the variable / function name from inside a $( ) or ${ } reference.
Scanning begins just past the opening delimiter and stops at the matching
closing delimiter (tracking nesting depth so an inner reference's closer is not
mistaken for the outer's) or at the first whitespace (which separates a make
function name from its arguments). Returns the leading name token; the empty
string when the reference is malformed (no content before a closer).
@End Reasoning
Process called "extract_delimited_name" takes text as Integer, start_pos as Integer, close_char as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let index be start_pos
    Let name be ""
    Let depth be 1

    Let open_char be 40
    If close_char is equal to 125:
        Set open_char to 123
    End If

    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If index is greater than or equal to length:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, index

            If ch is equal to open_char:
                Set depth to depth plus 1
                Set name to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with name, proc char_to_string from StringCore with ch
                Set index to index plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to close_char:
                    Set depth to depth minus 1
                    If depth is equal to 0:
                        Set scanning to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Set name to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with name, proc char_to_string from StringCore with ch
                        Set index to index plus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 32:
                        Note: Space ends the function/variable name token
                        Set scanning to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Set name to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with name, proc char_to_string from StringCore with ch
                        Set index to index plus 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return name
End Process

@Reasoning:
Scans a value/recipe string for $(NAME), ${NAME}, and $X references and appends
each referenced variable name to references_out. Balanced-delimiter tracking
lets nested references such as $(dir $(SRC)) record the outer name; the inner
reference is recorded on its own iteration because scanning continues past the
opening delimiter. Single-character references ($X, $@) record the one-byte
name. A function call like $(wildcard *.c) records "wildcard" as the leading
token, which is harmless because function names are validated against the
builtin set and never flagged. This mirrors makefile_to_hir's value parser so
the variable universe seen by analysis matches what translation produces.
@End Reasoning
Process called "extract_variable_references" takes text as Integer, references_out as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If references_out is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, index

        If ch is equal to 36:
            Note: '$' begins a reference
            Let next_index be index plus 1
            If next_index is less than length:
                Let next_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, next_index

                If next_ch is equal to 40:
                    Note: $( ... )
                    Let name be proc extract_delimited_name with text, next_index plus 1, 41
                    If proc string_length from StringCore with name is greater than 0:
                        proc list_append from List with references_out, name
                    End If
                    Set index to index plus 2
                Otherwise:
                    If next_ch is equal to 123:
                        Note: ${ ... }
                        Let braced_name be proc extract_delimited_name with text, next_index plus 1, 125
                        If proc string_length from StringCore with braced_name is greater than 0:
                            proc list_append from List with references_out, braced_name
                        End If
                        Set index to index plus 2
                    Otherwise:
                        Note: Single-character reference $X / $@ / $<
                        Let single be proc char_to_string from StringCore with next_ch
                        proc list_append from List with references_out, single
                        Set index to index plus 2
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Note: Trailing lone '$'
                Set index to index plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set index to index plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PHASE 1: DECLARATION COLLECTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records each target name from a rule's target list. When the target is ".PHONY"
its prerequisite list names targets that the user has declared phony; those
prerequisite names are added to the phony list (not the target list) because
they describe other rules rather than introducing a buildable target. All other
targets (including ordinary special targets like .SUFFIXES) record their names
in the target list so prerequisite resolution can find them.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_target_rule" takes analyzer as Integer, target_rule as Integer returns Integer:
    Let targets_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 8
    If targets_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let target_count be proc list_length from List with targets_list
    If target_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first_target be proc list_get from List with targets_list, 0
    Let is_phony_directive be 0
    If first_target is not equal to 0:
        Set is_phony_directive to proc string_equals from StringCore with first_target, ".PHONY"
    End If

    If is_phony_directive is equal to 1:
        Note: Prerequisites of .PHONY are the phony target names
        Let phony_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 16
        Let prereqs be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 16
        If prereqs is not equal to 0:
            Let prereq_count be proc list_length from List with prereqs
            Let p_index be 0
            While p_index is less than prereq_count:
                Let phony_name be proc list_get from List with prereqs, p_index
                If phony_name is not equal to 0:
                    proc list_append from List with phony_list, phony_name
                End If
                Set p_index to p_index plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Ordinary rule: record every target name
    Let target_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 0
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than target_count:
        Let target_name be proc list_get from List with targets_list, index
        If target_name is not equal to 0:
            proc list_append from List with target_list, target_name
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatches a single statement to the appropriate collector based on its NODE_*
kind. Target rules contribute target names (and, when the rule is .PHONY, the
prerequisites become phony entries); assignments and define blocks contribute
variable names; conditionals recurse into both branches.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_statement" takes analyzer as Integer, stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Let kind be proc node_kind_of with stmt
    If kind is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_TARGET_RULE:
        proc collect_target_rule with analyzer, stmt
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_SPECIAL_TARGET:
        proc collect_target_rule with analyzer, stmt
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT:
        Let var_name be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 8
        If var_name is not equal to 0:
            Let var_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 8
            proc list_append from List with var_list, var_name
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_DEFINE_BLOCK:
        Let define_name be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 8
        If define_name is not equal to 0:
            Let define_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 8
            proc list_append from List with define_list, define_name
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_CONDITIONAL:
        Let then_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with stmt, 32
        proc collect_makefile_declarations with analyzer, then_list
        Let else_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with stmt, 40
        If else_list is not equal to 0:
            proc collect_makefile_declarations with analyzer, else_list
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks the top-level statement list once and records every declared target,
variable, and .PHONY entry into the analyzer's collection lists. Conditionals
are descended into (both branches) so names defined inside ifeq/ifdef blocks are
visible to phase-2 validation. This pass performs no validation; it only builds
the symbol universe.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_makefile_declarations" takes analyzer as Integer, statements_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If statements_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from List with statements_list
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from List with statements_list, index
        proc collect_statement with analyzer, stmt
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PHASE 2: VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Extracts every variable reference from a value/command/operand string and warns
on any name that is neither defined in the makefile nor a built-in make
variable. A null or empty value short-circuits. The temporary reference list is
created per call so references from one value never leak into another.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_value_references" takes analyzer as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let value_len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
    If value_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let references be proc list_create from List
    proc extract_variable_references with value, references

    Let variable_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 8

    Let ref_count be proc list_length from List with references
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than ref_count:
        Let ref_name be proc list_get from List with references, index
        If ref_name is not equal to 0:
            Let is_defined be proc string_list_contains with variable_list, ref_name
            If is_defined is equal to 0:
                Let is_builtin be proc is_builtin_make_variable with ref_name
                If is_builtin is equal to 0:
                    Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with "Reference to undefined variable '", ref_name
                    Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with msg, "'"
                    proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, msg
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves one prerequisite name. It is satisfied when it names a known target
(an explicit rule) or has the shape of a source file (contains a '.' extension
or a '/' path separator, which make builds via implicit/pattern rules). A bare
name that is neither a known target nor file-shaped is recorded on the
undefined-targets list and warned, because make would fail with "No rule to
make target" at build time. Names containing '$' are skipped because they are
variable references resolved at expansion time, not literal prerequisites.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_prerequisite" takes analyzer as Integer, prereq as Integer returns Integer:
    If prereq is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let prereq_len be proc string_length from StringCore with prereq
    If prereq_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Skip variable-reference prerequisites; resolved at expansion time
    Let has_dollar be proc contains_char with prereq, 36
    If has_dollar is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let target_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 0
    Let is_known_target be proc string_list_contains with target_list, prereq
    If is_known_target is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: File-shaped prerequisites are buildable via implicit rules
    Let has_dot be proc contains_char with prereq, 46
    If has_dot is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let has_slash be proc contains_char with prereq, 47
    If has_slash is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Unresolved: neither a known target nor file-shaped
    Let undefined_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 40
    Let already_recorded be proc string_list_contains with undefined_list, prereq
    If already_recorded is equal to 0:
        proc list_append from List with undefined_list, prereq
        Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with "Prerequisite '", prereq
        Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with msg, "' names no known target and is not a file"
        proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, msg
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates one recipe line. A recipe whose command is empty (after the tab) is a
warning because make treats a blank recipe line as a no-op that usually signals
a copy/paste error. The command's $(VAR) references are validated against the
variable universe. The silent (@) and ignore-errors (-) flags need no check;
they are always syntactically valid prefixes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_recipe_line" takes analyzer as Integer, recipe as Integer returns Integer:
    If recipe is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let command be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with recipe, 8
    If command is equal to 0:
        proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, "Empty recipe line"
        Return 1
    End If

    Let command_len be proc string_length from StringCore with command
    If command_len is equal to 0:
        proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, "Empty recipe line"
        Return 1
    End If

    proc validate_value_references with analyzer, command
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates one target rule. The checks: (1) prerequisite resolution — each
non-pattern prerequisite must name a known target or a plausible source file,
otherwise it is recorded as an unresolved reference and warned; (2) recipe
validity for each recipe line; (3) an empty single-colon, non-pattern target
with neither prerequisites nor a recipe is warned because it is almost always a
mistake. .PHONY directive lines are skipped here and validated by
validate_phony_targets.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_target_rule" takes analyzer as Integer, target_rule as Integer returns Integer:
    Let targets_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 8
    If targets_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first_target be proc list_get from List with targets_list, 0
    Let is_phony_directive be 0
    If first_target is not equal to 0:
        Set is_phony_directive to proc string_equals from StringCore with first_target, ".PHONY"
    End If

    If is_phony_directive is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_pattern be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 40
    Let is_double_colon be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 48

    Note: Prerequisite resolution (skip for pattern rules whose prereqs use %)
    If is_pattern is equal to 0:
        Let prereqs be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 16
        If prereqs is not equal to 0:
            Let prereq_count be proc list_length from List with prereqs
            Let p_index be 0
            While p_index is less than prereq_count:
                Let prereq be proc list_get from List with prereqs, p_index
                proc validate_prerequisite with analyzer, prereq
                Set p_index to p_index plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Note: Recipe-line validity
    Let recipes_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 32
    If recipes_list is not equal to 0:
        Let recipe_count be proc list_length from List with recipes_list
        Let r_index be 0
        While r_index is less than recipe_count:
            Let recipe be proc list_get from List with recipes_list, r_index
            proc validate_recipe_line with analyzer, recipe
            Set r_index to r_index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Empty single-colon, non-pattern target with no prereqs and no recipe
    If is_pattern is equal to 0:
        If is_double_colon is equal to 0:
            Let prereqs_check be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 16
            Let recipes_check be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with target_rule, 32
            Let prereq_n be 0
            If prereqs_check is not equal to 0:
                Set prereq_n to proc list_length from List with prereqs_check
            End If
            Let recipe_n be 0
            If recipes_check is not equal to 0:
                Set recipe_n to proc list_length from List with recipes_check
            End If
            If prereq_n is equal to 0:
                If recipe_n is equal to 0:
                    If first_target is not equal to 0:
                        Let empty_msg be proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with "Target '", first_target
                        Set empty_msg to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with empty_msg, "' has no prerequisites and no recipe"
                        proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, empty_msg
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatches a statement to the matching validator. Target rules check
prerequisite resolution and recipe validity; assignments and define blocks
check their value for undefined-variable references; conditionals validate both
branches and their operand expressions. Include / export statements need no
per-statement check beyond what phase 1 collected.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_statement" takes analyzer as Integer, stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Let kind be proc node_kind_of with stmt
    If kind is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_TARGET_RULE:
        proc validate_target_rule with analyzer, stmt
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_SPECIAL_TARGET:
        proc validate_target_rule with analyzer, stmt
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT:
        Let value be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 24
        proc validate_value_references with analyzer, value
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_DEFINE_BLOCK:
        Let content be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 16
        proc validate_value_references with analyzer, content
        Return 1
    End If

    If kind is equal to NODE_CONDITIONAL:
        Let operand1 be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 16
        proc validate_value_references with analyzer, operand1
        Let operand2 be proc memory_get_pointer from Memory with stmt, 24
        proc validate_value_references with analyzer, operand2

        Let then_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with stmt, 32
        proc validate_makefile_statements with analyzer, then_list
        Let else_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with stmt, 40
        If else_list is not equal to 0:
            proc validate_makefile_statements with analyzer, else_list
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Re-walks the top-level statement list and validates each statement against the
symbol universe built in phase 1. Conditionals recurse into both branches so
statements inside conditional blocks are validated identically to top-level
ones.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_makefile_statements" takes analyzer as Integer, statements_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If statements_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from List with statements_list
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from List with statements_list, index
        proc validate_statement with analyzer, stmt
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates the .PHONY directive contents collected in phase 1: each name listed
under .PHONY should correspond to a target that actually has a rule, otherwise
the .PHONY entry is dead (it marks a non-existent target as phony). A missing
target for a phony name is a warning, not an error, because a .PHONY entry for a
not-yet-written target is a legitimate (if premature) pattern.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_phony_targets" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let phony_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 16
    If phony_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let target_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 0

    Let count be proc list_length from List with phony_list
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let phony_name be proc list_get from List with phony_list, index
        If phony_name is not equal to 0:
            Let has_target be proc string_list_contains with target_list, phony_name
            If has_target is equal to 0:
                Let msg be proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with ".PHONY names target '", phony_name
                Set msg to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with msg, "' which has no rule"
                proc add_makefile_validation_warning with analyzer, msg
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL ANALYSIS DRIVER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Runs the full two-phase analysis on a parsed makefile AST using a pre-created
analyzer. Phase 1 collects every declaration; phase 2 validates references and
.PHONY consistency. Returns 1 when analysis completed with zero errors, 0 when
the AST is missing/ill-formed or any error was recorded. The makefile_ast is
the NODE_MAKEFILE root whose statement list lives at offset 8.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_makefile" takes analyzer as Integer, makefile_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If makefile_ast is equal to 0:
        proc add_makefile_validation_error with analyzer, "Null makefile AST"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind be proc node_kind_of with makefile_ast
    If kind is not equal to NODE_MAKEFILE:
        proc add_makefile_validation_error with analyzer, "AST root is not a makefile node"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let statements_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with makefile_ast, 8

    Note: Phase 1: collect declarations
    proc collect_makefile_declarations with analyzer, statements_list

    Note: Phase 2: validate references, recipes, and .PHONY consistency
    proc validate_makefile_statements with analyzer, statements_list
    proc validate_phony_targets with analyzer

    Let error_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 24
    Let error_count be proc list_length from List with error_list
    If error_count is greater than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
One-shot convenience entry: creates an analyzer, runs the full analysis, and
returns the analyzer pointer so the caller can read errors/warnings via the
accessors below. Returns 0 only on allocation failure; a makefile with errors
still returns a valid analyzer carrying the diagnostics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_analyze" takes makefile_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let analyzer be proc create_makefile_semantic_analyzer
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc analyze_makefile with analyzer, makefile_ast
    Return analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated error list (offset 24) for the driver / IDE.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_get_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 24
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated warning list (offset 32) for the driver / IDE.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_get_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the list of unresolved prerequisite names (offset 40) so tooling can
report "No rule to make target" candidates ahead of an actual build.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_get_undefined_targets" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 40
End Process

@Reasoning:
Boolean wrapper over the error list so callers expressing "did analysis fail?"
do not need to compare a count. Returns 1 when any error was recorded, 0
otherwise.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_has_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let error_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 24
    Let count be proc list_length from List with error_list
    If count is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the count of warnings recorded, for summary reporting.
@End Reasoning
Process called "makefile_semantic_warning_count" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let warning_list be proc memory_get_integer from Memory with analyzer, 32
    Return proc list_length from List with warning_list
End Process
